args:
The scene: An Alberian city. As people lament
the turmoil in their kingdom, they hear rumors
from a former Dyrenell soldier that the seventh
scion has been possessed by the Other. Amidst
a backdrop of distrust towards the royal family,
rumors race like wildfire across the land.
Keep yer eyes peeled, boys!\nThey might have coin stashed away!
Please, you already took so much!\nAny more will ruin me!
Ain't my problem, boyo. If ya wanna hate\nsomeone, look to this kingdom what won't\nprovide work or bread for the masses.
The paddies and fields... My home...\nIt's all been washed away.
How are we to live now?
Thieves again, I hear.\nA bunch of shops and storehouses got hit.\nHow many cases is that this month?
I hear there was a town destroyed nearly\novernight by some kind of ghastly fiend.\nThese times are frightful ones indeed.
Everything's been a complete mess since\nwe became the damn Dyrenell Empire.\nWhat are the guards even DOING?!
Passing strange, if you think about it.\nKing Aurelius bringing back the very\nempire that revered the Other?
Yeah. And Prince Leonidas and Princess\nChelle are still shut away in their own\ncities, not saying a thing...
Also, I hear Prince Phares has gone\nmissing. Just what is going on?

And what happened to the seventh scion?
Didn't he sneak into the capital so he
could challenge Zethia to some kind of
decisive showdown?
Yeah, that IS strange! You'd think the\nwinner would be strutting about and\ncrowing over their great victory.
Hmph. The whole thing's just a sibling\nquarrel to them. They don't care what\neffect it has on us.
If you seek news on the seventh scion,\nthen I am your man.
Ha! You've got some nerve to show your\nface in here when your people are the\nreason our lives have been so hard!
Save your bellyachin' for the people in\ncharge, not the grunts. Or EX-grunt,\nin this fellow's case.

I, too, am a victim of the royal family.
My unit was suddenly disbanded and
left to fend for ourselves without coin
or provisions.
Sounds like you've had it hard as the rest.\nNow what's this news about the prince?
Right. I heard this from my former superior\nofficer. You see, the prince...
They say he returned to this world.
Well, I suppose the story DOES add up.\nSo the Other came back...
And not only was King Aurelius possessed\nby the Other, but so was Princess Zethia...
So that's why the kind Auspex suddenly\nbecame the cruel Empress...
It must be because of the Other's power\nthat we've had so many fiends showing\nup lately. Frightful stuff, that!

And now it's Prince {player_name}
who's been...
No wonder they don't want to tell
us anything.
I'll tell ya what it means:\nThe Other and the dragonblood royals\nare all monsters of the same ilk!
...Hey, keep this a secret, yeah?\nMum's the word!
Well, I have it on very good authority\nthat the Seventh Scion...
